</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C379F6D4FFE2FFB6E0FDF911DB07F883" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDCA55FFFE2FFB6E0FDF911DB07F883" blockId="1.[151,1437,1041,1822]" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">
<emphasis id="B917794DFFE2FFB6E0FDF911DF48F948" bold="true" box="[199,315,1725,1750]" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C63DEDCFFE2FFB6E179F911DFACF948" authority="Xue &amp; Zhang, 2018" authorityName="Xue &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2018" box="[323,479,1725,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Lambirocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B917794DFFE2FFB6E179F911DFACF948" box="[323,479,1725,1750]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">Lambirocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C63DEDCFFE2FFB6E24FF911DA60F948" authority="Maldonado-Capriles" authorityName="Maldonado-Capriles" box="[629,1043,1725,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraidioscopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B917794DFFE2FFB6E24FF911DD56F948" box="[629,805,1725,1750]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">Paraidioscopus</emphasis>
Maldonado-Capriles
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C63DEDCFFE2FFB6E41FF912DADBF948" box="[1061,1192,1725,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraidioscopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tagalicus">
<emphasis id="B917794DFFE2FFB6E41FF912DA40F94B" box="[1061,1075,1726,1749]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B917794DFFE2FFB6E478F911DADBF948" box="[1090,1192,1725,1750]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">tagalicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C63DEDCFFE2FFB6E4DBF912DB39F948" authorityName="Viraktamath" authorityYear="1973" box="[1249,1354,1725,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraidioscopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harrisi">
<emphasis id="B917794DFFE2FFB6E4DBF912DA9CF94B" box="[1249,1263,1726,1749]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B917794DFFE2FFB6E4C4F911DB39F948" box="[1278,1354,1725,1750]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">harrisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in the slender aedeagus and forewing venation, but this new genus can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C63DEDCFFE2FFB6E4A2F94DDB3BF964" box="[1176,1352,1761,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraidioscopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B917794DFFE2FFB6E4A2F94DDB3BF964" box="[1176,1352,1761,1786]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="186">Paraidioscopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the broad style, having a lamelliform lobe at the bend and the aedeagus apex bifurcate, without elongate processes.
</paragraph>
